Single.Single: This rung is for managing the possible conditions for triggering an agitation cycle. All cases require the agitator to be enabled. - Manual agitation triggered by a maintenance function. - Stirring the ice, which is triggered when the max sensor is reached to make sure there isn't a void in the hopper. - Auto agitation, which is managed by an idle timer, configured in the settings.
// The Agitator function block is for managing the agitator in the hopper.
// The agitator needs to run a agitator "cycle", called the agitator sequence, periodically to make sure
// the ice doesn't stick together. The agitator also runs while feeding ice, and stirs the ice when full
// to make sure there aren't any voids in the hopper making you think the hopper is totally full.
ManualAgitate: BOOL; // A bit to manually agitate, controlled from an HMI button exposed for maintenance functionality.
StirIce: BOOL; // A bit to manually agitate after reaching the max sensor.
FeedIce: BOOL; // A bit to run the agitator when feeding ice.
AutoAgitate: BOOL; // A bit to activate auto agitating cycle.
ReverseTime: TIME; // Agitator cycle time spent in reverse motion.
DwellTime: TIME; // Agitator cycle time spent dwelling between reverse-forward motion.
ForwardTime: TIME; // Agitator cycle time spent in forward motion.
IdleTime: TIME; // Time spent idling between automatic agitator cycles.
Agitating: BOOL; // A helper bit to indicate agitating is active.
Forward: BOOL; // Agitator motor VFD forward.
Reverse: BOOL; // Agitator motor VFD reverse.
CycleComplete: BOOL; // A bit that pulses everytime an agitate cycle completes.
SinceLastAgitate: TIME; // Time since the last agitate cycle completed.
